==English==
===Etymology===
From the Old Testament, Hebrew, urim ''lights'', thummim ''perfections''

===Noun phrase===
'''[[Urim]] and [[Thummim]]'''

#A divination medium or process used by ancient Hebrews (usually Israelites) in revealing the will of God on a contested point of view or other problem.

